                "Simulate the path to get the 7 increasing indices; since moves are only down/right, the visited positions are in left-to-right digit order, so you only need to check those 7 digits are non-decreasing.",
                "Use digit dynamic programming with states <code>pos</code> (0..15), <code>tight</code> (0/1), <code>cnt</code> (how many path digits placed 0..7), and <code>prev</code> (previous path digit 0..9); when <code>pos</code> is a path index, require the chosen digit >= <code>prev</code> and advance <code>cnt</code>.",
                "Compute <code>f(N)</code> = count of good numbers <= <code>N</code> and return <code>f(r) - f(l-1)</code>."
